            },
            "answer_text": "Many countries that are authoritarian in nature use, and have used, \"Democratic\", or \"Democratic Republic of\", even when they're anything but that. Some notable examples are the DPRK(Democratic peoples Republic of Korea) and the DRC(Democratic Republic of Congo). In my opinion, countries that utilise this in their name are just trying to sound good; it doesn't actually mean that the country in question is more democratic, and it's actually a pretty useful indicator as to which countries are oppressive.Tl;dr- it's a PR stunt for oppressive regimes to have nice names. Doesn't actually mean anything. ",
