            "answer_text": "There were regular elections to the parliament and other civil bodies, which made it a democracy. It\u2019s as simple as that. The UK is also a democracy, but it is a monarchy (the Head of State is not elected). The USA has gerrymandered electorates (which means, inter alia, that a candidate can get 3 Million votes more than her opponent, but still not be elected), but it is still called a democracy. Democracy means different things to different people - we can\u2019t judge others by our standards (particularly when some of our own standards are highly questionable). ",
